===Etymology===
From {{L.}} '''[[metaphysica]]''' < Byzantine Greek '''{{polytonic|[[μεταφυσικά]]}}''' (metaphusika) < {{AGr.}}  '''{{polytonic|[[μετά]]}}''' (meta) "after" + '''{{polytonic|[[φυσικός]]}}''' (phusikos) "natural".  The word derives from the title of the collection by Aristotle "μετὰ τὰ φυσικά" (after the natural things), titled because Aristotle believed that ontological philosophy should come after natural philosophy (φυσικά).  Contrary to common belief, the μετά in this case simply means "after" and not "beyond".  

